# Java Spring Code Quality

Use Java 21 or newer unless the project explicitly uses another version.

Use Spring Boot 3 or newer unless constrained by existing project requirements.

Code must be readable, explicit, and maintainable.

## Structure

Prefer package-by-feature or package-by-bounded-context over package-by-technical-layer.

Good:
```text
com.company.app.order
  api
  application
  domain
  infrastructure
Avoid global dumping grounds:
Plaintext

Копировать код

com.company.app.service
com.company.app.util
com.company.app.dto
com.company.app.repository

Controllers
Controllers must:
validate requests
delegate to application services
map responses
not contain business logic
not manage transactions directly
Application Services
Application services must:
orchestrate use cases
define transaction boundaries
call domain logic
call repositories and ports
avoid leaking infrastructure details
Domain
Domain code should not depend on Spring when avoidable.
Domain logic should be testable without application context.
Persistence
Do not expose JPA entities directly through APIs.
Use repositories only within owning module/context.
Avoid cross-context repository access.
Use optimistic locking where concurrent updates are possible.
DTOs
Use records for simple immutable DTOs.
Validate incoming DTOs using Jakarta Validation.
Do not reuse persistence entities as DTOs.
Transactions
Keep transactions short.
Do not call slow external systems inside database transactions.
Use outbox pattern for reliable event publication after database changes.
External Calls
External clients must define:
timeout
retry policy
error mapping
metrics
tests
Retries must be safe and idempotent.
Tests
For every new use case, add tests at the right level.
Do not use only SpringBootTest for everything.
Prefer focused tests.
